criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

  1. Children aged 5 - 15 years;

  2. MRI changes consistent with a diagnosis of FCD type II a or b;

  3. History of continuing seizures for less than 5 years;

  4. History of at least two epileptic seizures in the past 6 months before randomisation;

  5. Seizure semiology consistent with focal onset, agreed after pre-surgical discussion
     to be surgically treatable;

  6. Failure of at least two AEDs to control the seizures;

  7. Parent/ legal representative willing to give consent-

Exclusion Criteria:

Patient with the following characteristics will be excluded from the trial:

  1. Previous use of the KD;

  2. Not a surgical candidate for FCD resection;

  3. Administration of the KD is medically contraindicated. -
